    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="573"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7442/56</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Chargé in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Canadian Secretary of State for External
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bennett</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="44" xml:id="d573fn44">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Minister in Canada as an enclosure to his despatch No. 7, August 30,
                        1930; received September 8.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-18">August 18,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 804</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department of External
                    Affairs’ note No. 71 of June 19, 1930, and to previous correspondence regarding
                    the Aviation Radio Conference held in New York on April 10 and 11, 1930, I have
                    the honor, upon instructions from my Government, to advise you that on August 5,
                    1930, the Federal Radio Commission adopted the recommendations of that
                    Conference and will put them into effect as soon as practicably possible.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">B. Reath Riggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
